The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 East Bengal medio Mehtab Hossain has been ruled out of the clubs forthcoming outing at the 29th Federation Cup football tournament to be held in Ludhiana from Tuesday. 

 Mehtab, who was suffering from a groin injury, will not be available for the meet, said coach Subrata Bhattacharya, on Friday. East Bengal will face city rival Mohammedan Sporting in their inaugural match on Tuesday. 

 In another development, N.S. Manju and Shivmarayan Govind have signed for Mohun Bagan on Friday. 

 BPCL 1 emerged winners of the board A event in the IOCL-organised XXVIII PSPB Inter-Unit Bridge Tournament at the Tollygunge Club on Friday. ONGC B finished second.

 ATHLETICS: 57th State Championships: Day III action at the Salt Lake Stadium from 6am

 BRIDGE: PSPB Inter-Unit meet at Tollygunge Club.




